<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 2. Female Anthidiellum ignotum Engel, 2009 A, B lateral habitus and mesosoma of the \" less melanized \" individual (BSRU-AA- 1250) C, D lateral habitus and mesosoma of an individual with a black scutellum mark (BSRU-AA- 6709) E female faces and metasoma, showing variations of black infused stigma. From left to right: BSRU-AA- 2668, 1250, 1249, 6708, 6709, and CMU- 0013. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B) or 1 mm (C, D)." , "Figure 4. Males of Anthidiellum phuchongensis sp. nov. holotype (BSRU-AB- 0161) (left) and A. ignotum Engel, 2009 (BSRU-AA- 6707) (right) A, B dorsal habitus C, E lateral habitus D, F metasoma G, H face. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B, C, E) or 1 mm (D, F, G, H)." , "Figure 3. Female of Anthidiellum phuchongensis sp. nov. (BSRU-AA- 6706) A dorsal habitus B mandible C face D metasomal apex E metasoma F propodeum G lateral habitus. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, G), 1 mm (B, D-G), or 0.5 mm (C)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/532063" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/532065" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/532064" .

